## Requirement 2

We need to deduce which of the two components is usually larger.

To determine that, let's break down each component individually.

1. Dividend - this is the amount that company pays to its shareholders (usually when company has excess money);

2. Current price - current price on the stock of the market;

3. Capital gains yield - general representation of growth of any type of financial security (including the shares).
